  "prompt": "Were any real sets built for The Lego movie?",
  "response": "Yes, real sets were built for \"The Lego Movie.\" While much of the film was created using computer-generated imagery (CGI), the production team did construct physical sets and models to help guide the animation process and capture certain scenes. These physical sets were made from real Lego bricks and were used to create stop-motion sequences and reference material for the animators. The combination of physical and digital techniques helped give the movie its unique and authentic Lego feel.",
